torch
Homonym Number:
Word Class: verb
Sense Number:
Definition:to seek out and take fish (esp. flounders and eels, by spear), or muttonbirds, by dazzling them with torchlight
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1935 Havelock, for flatfish The torchlight provided by strong torches, car-battery lamps, or flaxstick and tow, dipped in tar or oil and fired
